1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:01,400
<i> Are you back?</i>

2
00:00:01,433 --> 00:00:02,867
<i> Comeback is real.</i>

3
00:00:02,867 --> 00:00:05,633
<i> And this pretty face?
It's here for the long run.</i>

4
00:00:05,633 --> 00:00:08,567
<i>I thought you'd take care
of the stuff you bought.</i>

5
00:00:08,567 --> 00:00:10,567
<i> I definitely can't miss this.</i>

6
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:13,933
Luna is going to be a bit late.

7
00:00:13,933 --> 00:00:15,433
<i> She has a guest over.</i>

8
00:00:15,433 --> 00:00:16,733
<i> Who? Do you know who it is?</i>

9
00:00:16,733 --> 00:00:18,967
<i> I'm not sure, but it's a guy.</i>

10
00:00:18,967 --> 00:00:20,867
<i> With a view like this...</i>

11
00:00:20,867 --> 00:00:22,700
<i> I get why you left me.</i>

12
00:00:22,700 --> 00:00:24,800
I will never get back with you.

13
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:26,433
<i> I'm calling you mine.</i>

14
00:00:26,433 --> 00:00:28,467
<i> He went out of his way
to give you flowers</i>

15
00:00:28,467 --> 00:00:30,700
<i> because he's worried.</i>

16
00:00:30,700 --> 00:00:32,733
<i> Do you think that it's fair</i>

17
00:00:32,733 --> 00:00:34,933
<i>to run away from someone
who's sincere?</i>

18
00:00:34,967 --> 00:00:36,867
<i> Someone worried about you?</i>

19
00:00:36,867 --> 00:00:39,633
<i>- Wow!
- [BOTH CHUCKLE]</i>

20
00:00:39,633 --> 00:00:40,967
<i> What are we celebrating, Jade?</i>

21
00:00:42,133 --> 00:00:44,000
<i> Rice cakes
are your favorite, right?</i>

22
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:51,867
- Want some?
- You go first.

23
00:00:54,100 --> 00:00:56,633
[CHUCKLES] Is it good?

24
00:00:56,633 --> 00:00:57,733
[KIKO CHUCKLES]

25
00:01:00,700 --> 00:01:01,667
Mm.

26
00:01:02,233 --> 00:01:04,067
Oh, wait.

27
00:01:04,067 --> 00:01:05,700
I have something
to give you.

28
00:01:07,533 --> 00:01:09,833
- What is this?
- Open it!

29
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:17,767
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

30
00:01:17,767 --> 00:01:19,067
[CHUCKLES]

31
00:01:19,067 --> 00:01:25,067
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

32
00:01:25,067 --> 00:01:27,500
I will never forget that day.

33
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:31,800
We were so happy.

34
00:01:36,167 --> 00:01:38,833
Riding bikes together...

35
00:01:39,733 --> 00:01:42,267
Being under the table
together like this.

36
00:01:42,300 --> 00:01:49,267
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

37
00:01:52,567 --> 00:01:56,633
Times like that remind me
that I have a friend like you.

38
00:01:58,967 --> 00:02:02,167
Why are you getting
sentimental?

39
00:02:02,167 --> 00:02:03,567
Nothing.

40
00:02:03,567 --> 00:02:06,900
I just want to
make it up to you

41
00:02:06,900 --> 00:02:09,233
I feel like we haven't
really talked lately.

42
00:02:11,733 --> 00:02:13,867
- Jade.
- Kiko...

43
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:17,033
We made a promise
to be best friends again, right?

44
00:02:19,067 --> 00:02:23,033
That nothing can get in
the way of our friendship?

45
00:02:24,233 --> 00:02:25,867
Yes.

46
00:02:25,867 --> 00:02:28,067
Nothing will get in
the way of our friendship.

47
00:02:28,067 --> 00:02:34,900
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

48
00:02:34,900 --> 00:02:36,300
[BOTH CHUCKLE SOFTLY]

49
00:02:43,233 --> 00:02:50,200
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

50
00:03:42,967 --> 00:03:44,833
You don't have anything
scheduled for today.

51
00:03:44,833 --> 00:03:46,500
- Jade!
- Oh.

52
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:47,533
Wow!

53
00:03:47,533 --> 00:03:50,133
You're so sweet!

54
00:03:50,133 --> 00:03:51,433
Thank you!

55
00:03:51,433 --> 00:03:53,233
- Jade!
- Oh.

56
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:54,567
Another one?

57
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:57,167
Wait a minute.
It's not my birthday.

58
00:03:57,167 --> 00:03:59,233
What's with the flowers?

59
00:03:59,233 --> 00:04:00,267
[JADE CHUCKLES]

60
00:04:00,267 --> 00:04:01,433
Oh...

61
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,367
Edward?
Where'd he go?

62
00:04:10,433 --> 00:04:12,433
Oh, where are we going?

63
00:04:12,433 --> 00:04:17,933
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

64
00:04:17,933 --> 00:04:19,067
Thank you!

65
00:04:21,333 --> 00:04:24,100
What's up with all the flowers?

66
00:04:24,100 --> 00:04:31,067
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

67
00:04:38,867 --> 00:04:40,033
What is going on?

68
00:04:41,233 --> 00:04:43,133
Did you do this?

69
00:04:47,233 --> 00:04:48,333
What do you think?

70
00:04:51,233 --> 00:04:54,333
Come on, Edward.
What's all this for?

71
00:04:54,333 --> 00:04:55,867
Because I like you.

72
00:04:56,600 --> 00:05:03,367
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

73
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:04,467
Uh...

74
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:09,633
Wait.
Can we pause for a second?

75
00:05:10,933 --> 00:05:14,133
Things are moving
way too fast.

76
00:05:15,333 --> 00:05:17,467
Jade, this didn't
happen overnight.

77
00:05:18,267 --> 00:05:21,233
I've liked you
since we were kids.

78
00:05:23,233 --> 00:05:24,967
Those feelings never went away.

79
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:26,933
Mm.

80
00:05:29,233 --> 00:05:30,233
[INHALES]

81
00:05:30,233 --> 00:05:32,100
If you'll let me,

82
00:05:34,067 --> 00:05:35,933
I want to pursue you.

83
00:05:39,033 --> 00:05:40,200
May I?

84
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:48,933
Can I even stop you?

85
00:05:48,933 --> 00:05:50,267
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

86
00:05:51,100 --> 00:05:52,200
Nope.

87
00:05:52,667 --> 00:05:55,133
Why even ask?

88
00:05:55,133 --> 00:05:57,033
Out of courtesy.

89
00:05:57,033 --> 00:05:58,067
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

90
00:05:58,067 --> 00:06:03,933
["PANGHABANG IKAW"
BY DARREN ESPANTO PLAYING]

91
00:06:03,933 --> 00:06:07,600
But seriously, Edward

92
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:10,900
we're just starting
to be friends again.

93
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:16,067
It's okay.

94
00:06:16,967 --> 00:06:18,067
I'll wait.

95
00:06:18,567 --> 00:06:20,700
I'm going through
some rough patches.

96
00:06:20,700 --> 00:06:22,100
I'll be here for you.

97
00:06:23,167 --> 00:06:25,433
I can be really moody.

98
00:06:25,433 --> 00:06:27,533
Oh, great.
Just what we needed.

99
00:06:27,533 --> 00:06:29,967
- Edward!
- Jade!

100
00:06:33,067 --> 00:06:34,333
I don't know.

101
00:06:34,333 --> 00:06:37,233
I don't want to get
your hopes up.

102
00:06:37,233 --> 00:06:40,700
I don't want to hurt you again,
Edward.

103
00:06:43,033 --> 00:06:44,167
Okay.

104
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,733
At least you didn't say no.

105
00:06:47,733 --> 00:06:52,467
["PANGHABANG IKAW" CONTINUES]

106
00:06:52,467 --> 00:06:54,767
I promise I'll wait.

107
00:06:54,767 --> 00:06:56,100
No pressure.

108
00:07:03,333 --> 00:07:06,533
["PANGHABANG IKAW" CONTINUES]

109
00:07:06,533 --> 00:07:08,400
Thank you for the flowers.

110
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:15,333
["PANGHABANG IKAW" CONTINUES]

111
00:07:30,067 --> 00:07:37,033
["PANGHABANG IKAW" CONTINUES]

112
00:07:48,167 --> 00:07:49,167
Gio!

113
00:07:50,067 --> 00:07:52,700
Did Peter visit you?

114
00:07:52,700 --> 00:07:54,267
How did you know?

115
00:07:54,267 --> 00:07:56,667
Tell me the truth, Luna.

116
00:07:56,667 --> 00:07:58,533
Is he the reason
you left before?

117
00:08:00,333 --> 00:08:01,467
Gio...

118
00:08:04,567 --> 00:08:06,367
Am I that replaceable to you?

119
00:08:07,533 --> 00:08:08,467
Am I that disposable?

120
00:08:08,467 --> 00:08:10,033
Or were you seeing us
at the same time?

121
00:08:10,667 --> 00:08:11,800
That's not what happened,
Gio.

122
00:08:12,833 --> 00:08:14,233
Which is it?

123
00:08:15,833 --> 00:08:17,333
Did you move on that easily?

124
00:08:17,333 --> 00:08:19,133
Or did you cheat on me?

125
00:08:19,133 --> 00:08:20,600
It's hard to explain--

126
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,600
Then try to!

127
00:08:22,633 --> 00:08:24,633
It's not that simple.

128
00:08:25,867 --> 00:08:27,533
I think it is.

129
00:08:28,733 --> 00:08:31,700
You simply don't want
to tell the truth.

130
00:08:31,700 --> 00:08:38,633
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

131
00:08:38,633 --> 00:08:40,433
Whatever the truth is

132
00:08:41,867 --> 00:08:43,433
I'll find out eventually.

133
00:08:43,433 --> 00:08:50,400
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

134
00:08:50,833 --> 00:08:51,867
Gio!

135
00:08:51,867 --> 00:08:58,833
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

136
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:10,700
Hey, are you sure?
We're safe here, right?

137
00:09:11,733 --> 00:09:12,733
Yes.

138
00:09:12,733 --> 00:09:15,200
They're busy too.
They won't even notice us.

139
00:09:16,067 --> 00:09:19,067
Don't worry,
no one can see us here.

140
00:09:19,067 --> 00:09:20,467
I've hung out here
so many times,

141
00:09:20,467 --> 00:09:21,900
and no one has seen me.

142
00:09:21,900 --> 00:09:23,867
Well, no one's really looking
for me anyway.

143
00:09:25,833 --> 00:09:27,000
Are you sure?

144
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:28,833
Cheska...

145
00:09:29,533 --> 00:09:30,733
I'm invisible, right?

146
00:09:31,967 --> 00:09:33,267
[CHESKA] Justin...

147
00:09:33,267 --> 00:09:36,267
[HUFFS] Can you
at least tone down

148
00:09:36,267 --> 00:09:37,900
those dramatic lines of yours?

149
00:09:37,900 --> 00:09:39,567
We both know deep down

150
00:09:39,567 --> 00:09:41,200
you still care
about your family.

151
00:09:41,833 --> 00:09:43,700
That's exactly why we're having
this meeting, right?

152
00:09:45,767 --> 00:09:46,767
It's okay.

153
00:09:48,867 --> 00:09:50,133
Give me your phones.

154
00:09:51,900 --> 00:09:58,900
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

155
00:10:00,900 --> 00:10:03,033
I'm not familiar
with the whole property,

156
00:10:03,067 --> 00:10:04,500
but these parts?

157
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:06,667
These are correct.

158
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:09,633
But this one?

159
00:10:11,067 --> 00:10:12,233
Why's it highlighted in red?

160
00:10:15,533 --> 00:10:17,133
[LEON] I need answers, Dad.

161
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:20,233
<i> Help me find the answers.</i>

162
00:10:20,233 --> 00:10:27,200
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

163
00:10:41,233 --> 00:10:44,233
[MUSIC FADES]

164
00:10:47,033 --> 00:10:54,033
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

165
00:11:10,233 --> 00:11:13,900
<i> This is the only place near
where I saw them, Dad.</i>

166
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:18,700
<i> Maybe they went here.</i>

167
00:11:21,733 --> 00:11:28,667
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

168
00:11:28,667 --> 00:11:29,800
[METAL BOX OPENS]

169
00:11:32,067 --> 00:11:33,133
[METAL BOX CLOSES]]

170
00:11:43,867 --> 00:11:50,833
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

171
00:12:04,033 --> 00:12:05,300
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

172
00:12:05,300 --> 00:12:09,367
You know, there's only one way
to find the answer to that.

173
00:12:10,267 --> 00:12:11,700
- Let's go there.
- Let's go.

174
00:12:11,700 --> 00:12:13,367
- Come on, let's go.
- Hey, wait.

175
00:12:13,367 --> 00:12:15,967
- What if it's dangerous?
- It's okay, Trixie.

176
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:17,300
We'll handle this.

177
00:12:17,867 --> 00:12:19,000
Let's go.

178
00:12:20,167 --> 00:12:22,033
What, you're just going
to leave me here?

179
00:12:23,367 --> 00:12:25,000
- Come on.
- You can go there.

180
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:28,000
[GRUNTS IN FRUSTRATION]

181
00:12:30,933 --> 00:12:32,067
[JUSTIN EXHALES DEEPLY]

182
00:12:33,933 --> 00:12:39,300
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

183
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:40,400
[PHONE CLATTERS]

184
00:12:44,967 --> 00:12:51,933
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

185
00:12:55,433 --> 00:12:56,700
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

186
00:12:58,133 --> 00:12:59,167
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

187
00:13:06,233 --> 00:13:09,700
[LOUD BLOWING]

188
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:20,133
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

189
00:13:20,133 --> 00:13:22,200
[PHONE CHIMES]

190
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:32,033
[PHONE CHIMES]

191
00:13:32,033 --> 00:13:34,300
"Where are you?"

192
00:13:38,133 --> 00:13:40,000
[PHONE CHIMES]

193
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:43,800
"You're really not going
to show up anymore?"

194
00:13:45,767 --> 00:13:47,767
"Answer my call!"

195
00:13:49,967 --> 00:13:51,267
Who is this?

196
00:13:53,467 --> 00:13:59,200
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

197
00:13:59,233 --> 00:14:05,300
[TYPING]

198
00:14:08,233 --> 00:14:09,433
[EXHALES]

199
00:14:20,333 --> 00:14:21,300
[LIQUOR POURING]

200
00:14:21,300 --> 00:14:24,133
- [EDWARD] Hey, Dad.
- Hey, you're here.

201
00:14:24,133 --> 00:14:26,500
Yes, I'm here for you...

202
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:28,233
for all...

203
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:30,267
and for everyone.

204
00:14:30,267 --> 00:14:32,133
[LAUGHING]

205
00:14:32,133 --> 00:14:33,300
Are you okay?

206
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:35,400
Never been better.

207
00:14:36,267 --> 00:14:37,433
Alright, alright.

208
00:14:37,433 --> 00:14:39,333
Okay, wait. Uhm...
[MOUTH CLICKS]

209
00:14:39,333 --> 00:14:41,933
How's the contract?
Did Luna sign it?

210
00:14:42,900 --> 00:14:44,567
Uh, I don't know, Dad.

211
00:14:44,567 --> 00:14:46,833
Jade and I haven't talked
about it.

212
00:14:46,833 --> 00:14:48,900
What could be causing
the delay? It's been days.

213
00:14:49,933 --> 00:14:52,300
Maybe they're still
thinking about it, Dad.

214
00:14:52,300 --> 00:14:53,533
Just let them be for now.

215
00:14:55,167 --> 00:14:57,200
What is there still
to think about?

216
00:14:57,200 --> 00:15:00,267
I mean, Hotel 88 is already
drowning in debt.

217
00:15:00,267 --> 00:15:02,233
It could be taken
from them at any time.

218
00:15:03,433 --> 00:15:05,100
Well...

219
00:15:05,300 --> 00:15:10,400
Jade told me she heard Martin
talking to another investors.

220
00:15:11,133 --> 00:15:12,500
Another investor?

221
00:15:13,433 --> 00:15:14,533
Yeah.

222
00:15:15,167 --> 00:15:17,100
It looks like
they really need it.

223
00:15:17,100 --> 00:15:18,567
Aside from you,

224
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:21,200
they're still looking
for another investor.

225
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:28,200
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

226
00:15:33,867 --> 00:15:36,000
Okay, Dad, I'll leave you now.

227
00:15:36,033 --> 00:15:37,933
- Good night.
- Night.

228
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:44,600
[SLURPS]

229
00:15:47,133 --> 00:15:51,433
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

230
00:15:51,433 --> 00:15:53,200
I found something
at Sandro's house.

231
00:15:54,033 --> 00:15:55,167
A cellphone.

232
00:15:55,533 --> 00:15:57,933
I'm on my way, wait for me.

233
00:15:57,933 --> 00:16:04,900
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

234
00:16:11,367 --> 00:16:13,333
Mister! Mister! Mister!
Wait! Wait!

235
00:16:13,533 --> 00:16:15,267
Go! Go! Go!
Straight ahead! Straight ahead!

236
00:16:15,267 --> 00:16:19,600
[MOTORCYCLE ENGINE ROARING]

237
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:22,233
Come on,
let's get the motorcycle!

238
00:16:24,033 --> 00:16:25,300
[DOOR OPENS]

239
00:16:25,300 --> 00:16:27,400
Oh, Uncle Ronald, have you had
the chance to scan

240
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:29,000
the proposal I've sent to you?

241
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:30,633
Oh yes, I've read it.

242
00:16:30,633 --> 00:16:32,500
But I'll have my lawyers
do a final pass.

243
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:34,667
Of course! How about
a tour of the hotel?

244
00:16:34,667 --> 00:16:35,933
When would you like to do it?

245
00:16:35,933 --> 00:16:37,633
Ah...

246
00:16:37,633 --> 00:16:39,433
My wife's flight
has been rescheduled.

247
00:16:39,433 --> 00:16:41,033
She's Carmela, you know her.

248
00:16:41,033 --> 00:16:42,567
Yes, of course.

249
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:48,100
Uh... I intend to visit Hotel 88
with her if possible.

250
00:16:48,933 --> 00:16:51,767
Because... you value
her opinion?

251
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:53,400
Right.

252
00:16:53,867 --> 00:16:55,067
Always.

253
00:16:55,767 --> 00:16:58,667
I wouldn't be where I am
if it weren't for her.

254
00:17:00,100 --> 00:17:02,933
A woman's instinct
is just different.

255
00:17:03,900 --> 00:17:05,667
- Right, Sari?
- [SARI GIGGLES]

256
00:17:05,667 --> 00:17:06,633
Right.

257
00:17:06,633 --> 00:17:08,833
A woman's instinct
is just built different.

258
00:17:09,567 --> 00:17:12,567
I remember when I first met
my wife.

259
00:17:13,033 --> 00:17:14,467
She told me,

260
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:16,933
it was instinct that told her

261
00:17:16,967 --> 00:17:19,133
that I would be
the love of her life.

262
00:17:19,733 --> 00:17:20,867
[HUFFS]

263
00:17:20,867 --> 00:17:22,033
True enough.

264
00:17:23,500 --> 00:17:24,633
How about you, Martin?

265
00:17:24,833 --> 00:17:27,033
When you first met Sari
at the cemetery,

266
00:17:27,700 --> 00:17:29,467
were you able to realize that...

267
00:17:29,767 --> 00:17:30,900
she's the one?

268
00:17:30,900 --> 00:17:37,867
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

269
00:17:40,600 --> 00:17:42,167
The cemetery?

270
00:17:44,500 --> 00:17:45,533
Yes.

271
00:17:45,833 --> 00:17:47,933
The umbrella, the rain.

272
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:50,800
How romantic.

273
00:17:53,900 --> 00:17:57,833
[CHUCKLES] Martin is...
speechless, Uncle.

274
00:17:59,133 --> 00:18:01,700
Do you remember...
our first meeting?

275
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,833
It was at the cemetery.

276
00:18:04,900 --> 00:18:09,033
When you gave me an umbrella
in the middle of the rain.

277
00:18:09,033 --> 00:18:12,567
[ROMANTIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

278
00:18:12,567 --> 00:18:19,500
[RAIN PITTER-PATTERING]

279
00:18:34,800 --> 00:18:36,267
[SARI] That was the sign
I was asking for

280
00:18:36,267 --> 00:18:37,667
from the universe.

281
00:18:40,667 --> 00:18:42,000
Ever since then...

282
00:18:42,767 --> 00:18:46,033
I knew that you were
the one for me.

283
00:18:48,067 --> 00:18:50,767
That's why I started
to like you.

284
00:18:51,233 --> 00:18:52,967
And now,

285
00:18:54,067 --> 00:18:55,533
I already love you.

286
00:18:56,733 --> 00:18:58,033
[LAUGHS]

287
00:18:58,033 --> 00:19:05,000
[ROMANTIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

288
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:08,867
[CHUCKLING]

289
00:19:09,633 --> 00:19:11,267
- Let's eat. [CHUCKLES]
- [SARI CHUCKLES]

290
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:13,700
Eat well.

291
00:19:23,233 --> 00:19:30,267
[JUAN PANTING, COUGHING]

292
00:19:30,300 --> 00:19:37,233
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

293
00:19:42,833 --> 00:19:44,000
[JUAN GROANING]

294
00:19:44,733 --> 00:19:50,600
[JUAN COUGHING CONTINUES]

295
00:19:51,167 --> 00:19:52,633
[DOOR SLAMS OPEN]

296
00:19:53,133 --> 00:19:54,767
[ANDY] It's all your fault!

297
00:19:55,667 --> 00:19:57,700
If you had just opened
your mouth right from the start!

298
00:19:57,700 --> 00:20:00,633
Huh?! Then I could've gotten
my hands on the hotel first!

299
00:20:00,633 --> 00:20:03,567
[JUAN PANTING] I have no idea
what you're talking about!

300
00:20:03,967 --> 00:20:05,400
Believe me,
I don't know anything!

301
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:06,900
[ANDY] What do you mean
you know nothing, huh?

302
00:20:06,900 --> 00:20:08,867
How many do I have
to tell you that?!

303
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:11,100
- The treasure.
- [JUAN CHOKING]

304
00:20:11,100 --> 00:20:12,900
What do you know
about the treasure?!

305
00:20:12,900 --> 00:20:15,167
I don't know
what you're talking about!

306
00:20:15,167 --> 00:20:17,767
[PANTING] And...
How old are you?

307
00:20:18,633 --> 00:20:22,233
You still believe in treasure?
[COUGHING]

308
00:20:22,233 --> 00:20:25,133
You bastard! [GRUNTING]

309
00:20:25,133 --> 00:20:29,767
[JUAN GURGLING]

310
00:20:29,767 --> 00:20:32,167
- [ANDY GRUNTS IN ANGER]
- [COUGHING]

311
00:20:32,167 --> 00:20:34,367
I told you, I have nothing
to tell you

312
00:20:34,367 --> 00:20:36,100
because I don't know anything!

313
00:20:36,133 --> 00:20:38,300
Talk to me when you're ready
to talk.

314
00:20:39,433 --> 00:20:41,400
[JUAN COUGHING ] I don't know
anything about a treasure!

315
00:20:42,433 --> 00:20:44,367
So just let me go!

316
00:20:44,767 --> 00:20:46,667
Let me out of here already!

317
00:20:46,667 --> 00:20:50,933
[JUAN COUGHING, GROANS]

318
00:20:55,100 --> 00:20:56,733
You know, you really never
miss an opportunity,

319
00:20:56,733 --> 00:20:58,300
do you, Cheska?

320
00:20:58,300 --> 00:21:01,200
Of course!
You shouldn't waste materials!

321
00:21:02,067 --> 00:21:04,700
Can you check
if we're close?

322
00:21:05,633 --> 00:21:06,767
Hold on.

323
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:09,533
Trixie, can you check?

324
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:16,533
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

325
00:21:16,533 --> 00:21:18,133
[JUSTIN] Yes.

326
00:21:18,133 --> 00:21:19,467
It's there.

327
00:21:19,467 --> 00:21:20,733
[CHESKA] Are you sure?

328
00:21:20,733 --> 00:21:22,467
[JUSTIN] Yeah, let's go.

329
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:26,800
- Trixie?
- Yeah.

330
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:29,233
You haven't said a word.

331
00:21:29,233 --> 00:21:30,600
Are you alright?

332
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:31,733
I'm alright.

333
00:21:35,400 --> 00:21:36,633
Wait.

334
00:21:42,167 --> 00:21:47,733
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

335
00:21:47,733 --> 00:21:49,367
Oh my god!

336
00:21:51,333 --> 00:21:52,767
[CHESKA] It's just a vine.

337
00:21:55,467 --> 00:21:57,167
Sorry.

338
00:21:58,167 --> 00:21:59,333
[SIGHS]

339
00:21:59,767 --> 00:22:03,300
I think I'm not the only one
enjoying this.

340
00:22:03,767 --> 00:22:06,633
Cheska, does it look like
I'm having fun?

341
00:22:07,533 --> 00:22:09,367
I didn't say it was you.

342
00:22:11,733 --> 00:22:13,600
Oh, I'm sorry.

343
00:22:15,467 --> 00:22:17,633
So, is it here?

344
00:22:18,833 --> 00:22:20,200
Yes, it's that way

345
00:22:20,700 --> 00:22:22,333
Do you think...

346
00:22:22,333 --> 00:22:25,167
we'll see Juan...

347
00:22:25,167 --> 00:22:26,700
in the map mark?

348
00:22:26,700 --> 00:22:29,700
Why would the kidnappers
leave Juan in their property?

349
00:22:30,733 --> 00:22:32,733
No, I just thought about it.

350
00:22:32,733 --> 00:22:36,433
What if Juan left that?

351
00:22:36,867 --> 00:22:38,567
What if...

352
00:22:38,567 --> 00:22:40,533
he heard where the kidnappers
would take him

353
00:22:40,533 --> 00:22:42,467
so he marked the map.

354
00:22:42,467 --> 00:22:43,800
Right?

355
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:46,467
You have such
a wild imagination, Cheska.

356
00:22:46,467 --> 00:22:48,467
But think about it.

357
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:50,567
It's possible, isn't it?

358
00:22:51,433 --> 00:22:52,867
You're so stubborn.

359
00:22:53,533 --> 00:22:54,900
Give that to me.

360
00:22:57,267 --> 00:22:59,633
- I think it's over there.
- Yeah, right there.

361
00:22:59,633 --> 00:23:01,300
Alright, let's go.

362
00:23:01,300 --> 00:23:03,333
- Follow me.
- Trixie.

363
00:23:03,333 --> 00:23:05,233
Be careful. Trixie, be careful.

364
00:23:05,233 --> 00:23:06,733
You guys, too.

365
00:23:06,733 --> 00:23:11,967
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

366
00:23:11,967 --> 00:23:16,500
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

367
00:23:16,500 --> 00:23:20,700
We won't get what we want
unless we get inside Hotel 88.

368
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:24,233
I need to get rid of the owners.

369
00:23:24,267 --> 00:23:25,967
Most especially, Michael's kids.

370
00:23:27,633 --> 00:23:30,300
But you have nothing
to worry about.

371
00:23:30,933 --> 00:23:34,700
I guarantee you,
Hotel 88 will be ours.

372
00:23:34,700 --> 00:23:41,667
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

373
00:23:43,300 --> 00:23:45,900
I've talked to the ban. You
don't have to worry about them.

374
00:23:45,900 --> 00:23:47,867
<i> But I'm going to charge.</i>

375
00:23:47,867 --> 00:23:49,600
<i> These are burner phones.</i>

376
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:53,267
<i>No matter what happens,
don't talking.</i>

377
00:23:53,267 --> 00:23:54,533
<i> That's from the supplier.</i>

378
00:23:54,533 --> 00:23:56,367
<i>Ms. Jade's supplier
of happiness.</i>

379
00:23:56,400 --> 00:23:58,700
<i> - Sir Edward.
- It doesn't taste good.</i>

380
00:23:58,700 --> 00:24:03,000
<i>I think it's time to open up
to someone who likes me, too.</i>

381
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:05,300
<i> Can you really teach
your heart to like him?</i>

382
00:24:06,367 --> 00:24:09,467
- You're not coming with him!
- Mind your own business, Gio.

383
00:24:09,467 --> 00:24:11,667
-<i> You think I'm scared of you?
</i>- [GUN COCKS]

384
00:24:11,667 --> 00:24:13,733
You might get scared of this.

385
00:24:13,733 --> 00:24:15,833
<i> Fine, I'll go with you!</i>
